By Job Osazuwa To celebrate the 70th anniversary of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), its charity arm, His Love Foundation (HLF) will be dedicating two dialysis centres in the South East. As learnt, this will increase to 10 the total number of dialysis centres set up by the foundation across Nigeria. The new centres are the Enoch and Folu Adeboye Dialysis Centre at   Comprehensive Medical Centre, Awkuzu, Anambra State and the Enoch and Folu Adeboye Dialysis Centre at the University of Nigeria Teaching Hospital Enugu, Ituku-Ozalla, Enugu State. As disclosed by the foundation, each of the centres would have three units of dialysis machines, and a medical water reserve osmosis purification system, while the centre in Enugu would in addition have a power generation plant. The dialysis centre at Akwuzu would be dedicated on July 20 while that of Enugu is slated for July 22. The HLF stated that it had executed close to one million projects and had impacted over 166 million lives having in the last four years spent over N32 billion on its various projects nationwide. It added that the establishment of the centres was in fulfilment of its strategic objective of “help for the helpless; hope for the hopeless; food for the hungry and strength for the weak.”